From 3f6970e538bd6b038f5c31ef7ab84c3402702dac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 09:59:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 163/309] PCI: qcom: Override NO_SNOOP attribute for SC8280XP
 platforms

The SC8280XP PCIe controller can pass transactions with the NO_SNOOP
attribute set even though system memory is cache coherent.  This can make
DMA to cacheable memory fail coherency, leaving the CPU observing stale
cache lines after the endpoint has completed the DMA.

This is reproducible with a discrete NVIDIA GPU behind the SC8280XP root
complex: the GPU copy engine writes system memory and signals completion,
but the CPU readback still sees the old value, causing the driver copy
engine self-test to fail during device initialisation.

Use the existing NO_SNOOP override support for the SC8280XP configuration
so both read and write transactions are forced to snoop.

Fixes: 70574511f3fc ("PCI: qcom: Add support for SC8280XP")
Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
index 9cbe0aded..85deabb0e 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
@@ -1503,6 +1503,7 @@ static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_2_9_0 = {
 static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_sc8280xp = {
 	.ops = &ops_1_21_0,
 	.no_l0s = true,
+	.override_no_snoop = true,
 };
 
 static const struct qcom_pcie_cfg cfg_fw_managed = {
